              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "A reliability improvement trajectory is when both raw volume and normalised rate are declining quarter-over-quarter, recurrence rate is below 10%, and no single root cause category dominates more than 25% of incidents. Anything else is a treadmill: the team is working hard but not improving."
              }
            ]
