            "type": "text",
            "text": "Incident volume and trend analysis complements MTTx metrics by answering whether the reliability trajectory is improving, stagnant, or worsening. The core measurements are volume by severity over time, root cause distribution over a rolling 90-day window, and recurrence rate. Trend signals \u2014 declining volume, stable high volume, sudden spike, and increasing SEV-1 fraction \u2014 each have distinct causes and responses. Raw counts must be normalised by request volume and service scope to produce fair comparisons across growth periods. Monthly engineering reviews and quarterly leadership reviews convert trend data into investment decisions."
